===Earth ovens=== An [[earth oven]], or cooking pit, is one of the most simple and long-used cooking structures. At its simplest, an earth oven is a pit in the ground used to trap heat and bake, smoke, or steam food. Earth ovens have been used in many places and cultures in the past, and the presence of such cooking pits is a key sign of human settlement often sought by [[archaeologists]]. They remain a common tool for cooking large quantities of food where no equipment is available. {| class="wikitable sortable" |- ! Name ! class="unsortable"| Image ! Description |- | [[Barbecue]] | [[File:Barbecue pit.jpg|120px]] | Barbecue is both a cooking method and apparatus. * [[Pit barbecue]] – a method and constructed item for barbecue cooking meat and [[root vegetable]]s buried below the surface of the earth. <gallery class="center" caption="" mode=nolines widths="122px" heights="122px"> File:A_Southern_Barbecue.jpg|A pit barbecue </gallery> |- | [[Hāngi]] | [[File:Hangi prepare.jpg|120px]] | A traditional [[New Zealand]] [[Māori people|Māori]] method of cooking food using heated rocks buried in a [[pit oven]] still used for special occasions. |- | [[Horno]] | [[File:A Horno (an adobe oven) at Taos Pueblo in New Mexico in 2003.jpg|120px]] | |- |[[Huatia]] | | |- | [[Kalua]] | [[File:Roasted puaa.jpg|120px]] | |- | [[Pachamanca]] | [[File:Pachamanca Peru.JPG|120px]] | |- | [[Tandoor]] | [[File:Clay Pots.jpg|120px]] | |}
===Industrial ovens=== [[Industrial oven]]s are heated chambers used for a variety of industrial applications, including [[drying]], [[Curing (chemistry)|curing]], or [[baking]] components, parts or final products. Industrial ovens can be used for large or small volume applications, in batches or continuously with a conveyor line, and a variety of [[temperature]] ranges, sizes and configurations. {| class="wikitable sortable" |- ! Name ! class="unsortable"| Image ! Description |- | [[Batch oven]] | <!--[[File:EXAMPLE|120px]] --> | A type of [[furnace]] used for thermal processing. They are used in numerous production and laboratory applications. |- | [[Burn-in ovens]] | <!--[[File:EXAMPLE|120px]] --> | |- | [[Clean process oven]] | <!--[[File:EXAMPLE|120px]] --> | |- | [[Flame broiler]] | <!--[[File:EXAMPLE|120px]] --> | |- | [[Industrial oven]] | [[File:Industrial oven.jpg|120px]] | Pictured is an industrial convection oven used in the manufacture of aircraft components |- | [[Reach-in oven]] | <!--[[File:EXAMPLE|120px]] --> | |- | [[Walk-in/Truck-in ovens]] | <!--[[File:EXAMPLE|120px]] --> | |- | [[Spiral ovens]] | <!--[[File:EXAMPLE|120px]] --> | Ovens with a helical conveyor |}
===Kilns=== A [[kiln]] is a thermally insulated chamber, a type of oven, that produces temperatures sufficient to complete some process, such as hardening, drying, or chemical changes. Various industries and trades use kilns to harden objects made from [[clay]] into [[pottery]], [[brick]]s etc.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bioenergylists.org/stovesdoc/Goyer/Kilns/Goyer_Kilns_and_Brick_Making.pdf |title=Brick making kilns |format=PDF |date= |accessdate=2012-05-20}}</ref> Various industries use [[rotary kiln]]s for [[pyroprocessing]]—to calcinate ores, produce [[Cement kiln|cement]], lime, and many other materials. [[File:Rotary Kiln.jpg|thumb|A [[rotary kiln]]]] {| class="wikitable sortable" |- ! Name ! class="unsortable"| Image ! Description |- | [[Anagama kiln]] |<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Anagama Being Built.jpg|120px]] --> | An ancient type of [[pottery]] kiln brought to [[Japan]] from [[China]] via [[Korea]] in the 5th century. |- | [[Birch Creek Charcoal Kilns]] | [[File:Charcoal Kilns near Leadore.jpg|120px]] | |- | [[Brick clamp]] | [[File:India - Sights & Culture - Rural Brick Making Kiln 02 (4040024973).jpg|120px]] | |- | [[Cement kiln]] | [[File:KilnBZ.JPG|120px]] | |- | [[Lime kiln]] | [[File:Lime plant, Wyoming.jpg|120px]] | |- | [[Rotary kiln]] | [[File:RTC890 1725.jpg|120px]] | A [[pyroprocessing]] device used to raise materials to a high temperature ([[calcination]]) in a continuous process |- | [[Top-lit updraft gasifier]] | <!--[[File:EXAMPLE|120px]] --> | |- | [[Tube furnace]] | <!--[[File:EXAMPLE|120px]] --> | |- | [[Tybo Charcoal Kilns]] | <!--[[File:EXAMPLE|120px]] --> | |}
